[Black "Pawn Structures 3: Italian"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 { Now let's move on to the Italian. } 3... Bc5 4. c3
Nf6 5. d3
{ 5.d4  A very fashionable variation nowadays.  5...exd4  6.e5  d5  7.Bb5  Ne4  8.cxd4  Again, a very important and fashionable structure. In the center, White has the e5 and d4-pawns against d5. Of course, White, therefore, has a certain advantage in the center, but his d4-pawn is a bit weak so there are pluses and minuses. It can also get to the structure where White plays  8...--  9.Nc3  and Black takes:  9...Nxc3  10.bxc3  .  Or Black can play f6 with exf6 which would lead to another structure that also quite often arises on the board via various openings. }
5... O-O 6. O-O d5 7. exd5 Nxd5
{ Also a very fashionable line and important structure. In general, Black has a good space advantage and a healthy position but it is very tactical so he has to be careful with his e5-pawn as White has a lot of resources in these positions which we will study in detail. }
