{ I've also tried this continuation once or twice, but I am not sure whether it equalizes fully. }
9. g3 Nxc3
{ An important detail is that after  10.Qe1+  Black has  10...Qe7  . } 10. bxc3
Qg4 { 10...Qh3  is also an option. } 11. Re1+
{ Unfortunately for Black, the king has to move. If he had been able to castle short he wouldn't have had any problems, but White doesn't allow that to happen. Still, the position after  11...Kf8  12.Be2  Qf5  is not too bad for Black. ...h5 is an option, and the king is quite safe on f8. Nevertheless, White has a potential c3-c4 available too, and I was quite concerned about this line since I couldn't find full equality for Black. With new engines maybe new ideas will be found, but this line is the reason why I was relying mainly on 8... Nxc3. }
