13... Be8 { A very important counter. } 14. Qh3 { 14.Qh4  is also possible. }
14... dxc4
{ If not for ...Be8 and ...dxc4, the position could have been extremely unpleasant for Black. }
15. Bxc4+
{ Or  15.Bxf5  h6  and a sacrifice on h6 leads to nothing for White, perhaps a draw at best. }
15... Bf7
{ Black is just in time to coordinate the pieces and get an equal position. In the 8. Nc3 line, White may be able to get a certain degree of positional pressure in the long run, especially if Black doesn't respond precisely with move by move play and preparation. }
