O-O
{ It is important to note that this is an even better version @@StartBracket@@for Black@@EndBracket@@ of the 8. Qh5 line. }
11. Qxd5 Bc6
{ I think every single move has been tried now:  12.Qb3  ,  12.Qc4  ,  12.Qh5  . }
12. Qh5 g6 13. Qh3 Ng5
{ A similar story to the 8. Qh5 line - but without the c-pawns, which makes it easier for Black to equalize. The pawn on d4 is vulnerable, and if the theoretical ground work has been performed carefully, Black will just equalize. }
