{ Now ...g6 seems to work and it is also what I played back in the days. } 13.
Qxd5 Qc7
{ This is the important difference. With the c-pawns on the board, ...g6 would not be a good call, because White would simply take on d5 and be a pawn up. There are many options for White now:  14.c4  ,  14.Bh6  and other tries, all of which need careful inspection.In fact, at this moment there was a sad episode in my chess career, when I lost to Vishy Anand. In a long game and with precise play, Black should have been fine, but in my rapid game I got confused and lost quickly. I remember I spent a lot of time on this specific variation because it is a very principled line. At that time, I had the feeling that I was holding with Black in every single line and should be able to equalize against any attempt that White could throw in. The lesson is that you need to do a lot of work, and always need to be careful to remember the results of your analysis. }
