8... Nd7 9. O-O-O { Here, Black has tried almost all possible plans. } 9... Ne5
{ This is also a possibility. } 10. Kb1 Nxf3 11. gxf3
{ As strange as it may sound, this position is quite uncomfortable for Black. White's pawn structure is compromised but the open g-file offers great attacking chances. I studied these types of positions a lot as I was tempted to ruin my opponents structure and try to win a better endgame. It's hard to reach that endgame though, and White's initiative is of a long-term nature and pretty hard to face. }
