12... Qa5 13. d5
{ The latest trend, and important recent games are Nepomniatchi-Esipenko and Karjakin-Esipenko. With precise play, Black should hold.Concluding, I'd say that 6...Bd6 is not a very nice variation to play as Black, considering White has many ideas to fight for an advantage. But, on the other hand, play is very direct and if you prepare well, have a good memory and a powerful engine, it is possible you may hold the line. There is no strategic danger in this variation, only tactical. With White it's perfectly playable. 9. Re1, 9. cxd5, 9. Nc3: there are some prospects everywhere. That's why I've always preferred 6... Be7 myself. }
