Rxe1 Rd8 { Threatening ...Qxe1+ followed by ...Rxd6. } 20. Re3
{ So that the queen is no longer hanging on d6. } 20... h6 21. Qf4 Qxa2 22. d5
{ Black continues  22...Na5  , etc.  Of course, without computers, nobody would go for this line, as Black's position looks terribly dangerous. But nowadays the chess world is different and it seems Black is just in time to hold, which is vital for the entire evaluation of 7... Bf5. }
