9... Bg4
{ Another way to prevent White from playing d2-d4 is  9...Qf6  , but I'm not sure that the queen is so well-placed there. After  10.d3  Bb6  11.a4  White is a bit more comfortable. The idea of a4-a5 is annoying to deal with for Black.   Instead,  9...Bg4  is perhaps the most straightforward option for White. }
10. h3 Bh5 11. d3 f6
{ If Black gets the bishop to b6 and the queen to d7, he should be doing fine, but White has annoying possibilities that Black should reckon with. }
12. g4 Bf7 13. Nd2 { Intending to put the knight on e4. } 13... Qd7 14. Ne4
{ Activating the knight, followed by a2-a4 when Black retreats the bishop to b6. It's close to equal but I would prefer White as he is more active. }
