4... Bc5
{ This is a very solid option and probably the simplest way for Black to play against the 4. g3 system. I myself moved from  4...d5  to  4...Bc5  at some point, as there are less potential tactical problems to worry about and there is less theory. }
5. Bg2 d6 6. d3
{ I would advise White players to start with this move. It's not recommended to play  6.O-O  first, because in that case Black has additional possibilities such as  6...h5  followed by ...Bg4 and ...h4.   After  6.d3  there are a lot of games you can study in this variation. I think the position is equal. Of course, if I was asked whether I want to play White or Black here I would choose White, but the game is pretty much equal. }
6... a5
{ I saw that lately computers have been preferring this move over 6. .. a6. In the Lesson on the slow Italian, you'll see this idea as well - gaining space is important, whether you're White or Black.Of course, ...a6 looks safer, as you're probably not going to castle long if you advance the pawn to a5 instead. However, Black does gain the idea of advancing the pawn further to a4 with good play on the queenside. }
7. O-O O-O
{ It's also possible to try to exchange a pair of knights with  7...Nd4  followed by ...c6. White usually replies  8.h3  followed by Be3, or perhaps takes on d4 and then moves the king to h2, in order to prepare f2-f4. }
8. h3 { Understandable, as ...Bg4 is rather annoying. } 8... h6
{ Similarly, Black removes the possibility of White playing Bg5. } 9. Be3
{ Another move is  9.Kh2  with the idea to eventually play f2-f4, but this is not easy to achieve because after  9...Be6  ,  anytime the knight moves from f3, Black gets in ...d5 with play in the center. }
9... Bxe3 10. fxe3 Ne7
{ Black maneuvers the knight to g6 with a complicated but equal position.To sum up, it depends on your style of playing, but I prefer 4... Bc5 as reply to this system as the positions are easier to play than those after 4... d5. For White, the 4. g3 system is perfectly playable - you get complicated positions without too much theory. }
