[Black "2. Nc3 Nf6 3. g3 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5
{ I want to draw your attention to the fact that White can also play the g3 system starting with 2. Nc3. }
2. Nc3 Nf6 3. g3
{ In case of  3...d5  the game will likely transpose to the Four Knights with 4. g3. For example:  4.exd5  Nxd5  5.Bg2  Nxc3   @@StartBracket@@here there is the interesting option  5...Nf6!?  too@@EndBracket@@  6.bxc3  Bc5  7.Nf3  Nc6  and we've transposed. }
3... c6
{ This is rarely played but you'll need to analyze this if you want to start with 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. g3. Black just wants to continue ...d5, even after 4. Nf3. }
4. d4 { White's most dangerous reply. } 4... Bb4
{ I'm not sure whether this works, but I saw that this has recently been played by Ivanchuk and usually he knows what he's doing. So this is an interesting way for Black to face White's alternative move order. }
