6... d6 7. Ne2
{ This move has become fashionable, with the idea of transposing to a type of @@StartBracket@@slow@@EndBracket@@ Italian game. White wants to play c3, Ng3 and then at the right moment d4. It seems Black is facing some problems in this line, for example a game Anand-Mamedyarov which Vishy won a few years ago. It's not easy for Black to equalize here. }
7... Ne7 8. Ng3 c6 9. Ba4 Ng6 10. c3 Ba5
