{ A perfectly playable line, which can be deduced by the fact that a large number of games have been played in this position, leading to long theoretical discussions. White has tried almost every legal move in this position, and I will show some of them.Obviously, if you are on Black's side, you should become very familiar with the ensuing variations. If White manages to finish development, he will naturally be slightly better. Therefore, Black has to be very precise and push ...d5 in the right moment, which means he needs to know many forced lines. }
7. g3
{ A serious and logical attempt − White plans to develop with Bg2, O-O and stop ...d5. }
7... h5
{ Lately, ...h5 became popular and it is an interesting move. I played it in a blitz game against Sergei Rublevsky, Moscow 2007. Black has a straightforward plan, to push ...h5-h4 and play on the h-file. Of course, it is tricky to play the opening so ambitiously but if this decision is backed up by the engines and analysis, ...h5 could be another possibility for Black. }
