{ This often - but not necessarily - leads to an endgame which should be fine for Black. Another interesting choice is  8...Bb7  . After  9.c4  Nb6  play becomes very sharp. Black will castle long followed by ...Re8 and ...f6. This line should be placed under the engine's microscope, but it might be fine for Black. }
9. c4 Nb6 10. exd6 cxd6 11. Be3
{ Perhaps the best chance to fight for something. After  11.Nc3  Black attacks the c4-pawn with  11...Be6  , and after  12.b3  d5  Black seems to be able to equalize. }
11... d5 { The best move according to the computer. } 12. Nd2 dxc4 13. g3
{ White tries to develop the bishop to g2 and castle next. This position looks quite dangerous for Black but, maybe with very deep preparation, is just in time to equalize. Not an easy quest though. In short, 8... d6 is not the refutation of 8. h4 since the ensuing positions are not sterilized yet, and White can keep asking questions. }
