8... Qe6
{ The most popular move these days and I also played it once. I still don't see any advantage for White. }
9. Nd2 { Now Black has many different options. } 9... a5
{ This is considered to be the best move, anticipating White's developing plan starting with b3. At the same time, ...Ba6 is made possible.   It's also fine to play  9...Be7  10.Nf3  f6  . Black is playing natural, developing moves, and it is unclear whether White can get anything out of the opening even here. }
10. c4 Nb6 11. b3 a4
{ White's b3 will always be hit by ...a4, which is why 9. g3 has become the main try. }
