{ The main line and also a very direct way of playing. Instead,  10...d5  is a straightforward reaction, but it won't suffice for full equality:  11.exd6  Qxe4+  12.Nxe4  cxd6  13.b3  d5  14.cxd5  Nxd5  15.Bc4  . The material on the board is limited but White has a better pawn structure. And then again, with very accurate play, Black should be able to hold this position, which is still not equal. }
