{ White seems to have the upper hand here. } 12... Re8 13. f4 f6 14. a4
{ For illustrative purposes, the text move is a very important idea for White in these positions. The a5 threat is quite an unpleasant one for the knight on b6, which is currently in danger of being confined to a8. White is better. }
