11. b3 Bb4
{ This is the idea of Black's concrete play, especially since the setup with the knight on b6 and the bishop on a6 is not very appealing strategically. }
12. Bd2 Bxc3 13. Bxc3 d5
{ This was considered to be enough to equalize, but Kasparov analyzed the position deeper. }
14. Qh4 dxc4 15. Be2
