9. Nc3 Bb7
{ I played twice this setup in Wijk aan Zee 2011 against Shirov and Nepomniachtchi. I scored 1.5/2, but it is a very tricky yet risky system that requires a lot of analysis. It is playable but, as always, concrete variations should be known by heart and checked carefully.If you dare and have the impression that your opponent is not fully prepared, you can also gamble and go for this line, even though you haven't analyzed it in depth. We can have a look on how the game could develop further, not to give you certain theoretical pointers but to offer you a feeling and understanding of these weird positions. }
