11. Qf2
{ 11.Qd2  is also possible, but after  11...Nb6  White is equalizing at best. }
11... Nb6
{ It is possible to retreat the knight to either f6 or b6. The latter hasn't been refuted yet, though  11...Nf6  is the main move. }
12. Be2 dxe5 13. O-O
{ White's plan is to play for compensation, and indeed, play becomes very sharp. With accurate play, though, Black should get a decent position. Just to give you an idea, let's see a possible direction the game could take. }
13... Bg7 14. Ba3 Qe6
{ Now after  15.Nc3  taking  15...exf4  is an option, but generally, those positions are dangerous for Black. With precise play, backed up by the engines, Black should probably find a way to equalize. But I believe that 11... Nf6 is safer than 11... Nb6. }
