{ The most common reply. In this position, White has tried almost every legal move. The most popular is  11.h3  , as after most other moves it seems that Black can get in ...f6. For example  11.O-O  f6  when White will probably have to capture on f6 and then return the bishop to e2 at some point, in order to protect the knight on f3. }
11. h3 Bh5
{ Since we've seen that  11...Bxf3  is not that good,  11...Bh5  is the main move instead. I've played this myself more than once. Now again, White has tried almost every legal move in the position after  11...Bh5  . Even a move like  12.Rc1  has been played, even though I can't understand what it's trying to achieve - but apparently the computer likes it. }
12. O-O { This is an important move to know. } 12... f6
{ The first point is that after this move it's not so clear as before, because White has an extra resource 13. g4. }
13. g4
{ Regardless of where Black retreats the bishop - the point is that, should Black at some point now play ...fxe5, White can then first capture Bxc6 and afterwards recapture on e5 with the knight. }
