{ Almost all legal moves have been tried here for White. I cannot go into all of them - you should just review the top games with a computer engine. Strategically, the position is fairly simple, as Black just wants to finish development and then @@StartBracket@@at the right moment@@EndBracket@@ attack the center with ...f6. White, in turn, wants to make it difficult for Black to execute this plan by putting pressure on the e4-knight and d5-pawn. }
