12. Qb3
{ I wouldn't advise White to play this move, as Black can now get a dangerous position with a piece sacrifice. }
12... Bxf3
{ I'm not sure if White has anything after  12...Ne7  ,  just protecting the d5-pawn, but Black can also resort to tactics. }
13. gxf3 Nxf2
{ White has only one good way of replying to this piece sacrifice. } 14. Bxf2
Nxd4 15. Bxd4 Qh4+
{ Now after  16.Kd2  a strange position arises. Black can recapture on  d4  with either the queen or bishop. The computers prefer to recapture  16...Bxd4  . White tries to get the king to safety with  17.Kc2  . Black solidifies his position with  17...c6  18.Bd3  and then takes the e5-pawn  18...Bxe5  . Black has three pawns for the piece. Objectively it's equal, but I would prefer to play this as Black. }
