{ White wants to, at some point, play Ne3, but then Black always has d5. And then a slow game will arise where sometimes White is playing Bc2 and it's not easy for Black to find any clear counterplay, but he has a solid position.So all in all, I think it's perfectly playable for Black. I still prefer to be White in this position, but White will only have a slightly more comfortable game, and I wouldn't say that White is necessarily better in this position. I think that this is the most promising system against Nf6 d3 h6 unless one day it will be refuted. Who knows? Because there are so many games where already many strong players are playing it with Black and, nobody has come close to refuting this system. }
