4. Nc3 Nf6 5. d3
{ I played this myself twice, once against Aronian in Candidates Tournament 2018, Berlin; which was actually a very entertaining game. The second one was in 2019, I believe both times I didn't get anything out of the opening. }
5... d6 6. Na4 Bb6 7. c3
{ Not actually hurrying to take this bishop right now, but rather later and getting Bb3-Bc2 with some slight advantage due to the pair of bishops. There is a game; Karjakin - Grischuk from the Candidates 2018 where Alexander Grischuk managed to equalize slowly, making a draw. But I think even more accurate is just to go a6 and Nd5 as Black, simply wanting to get d6-h6 with normal play. }
