3... a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O
{ Here are a lot of main systems that I will explain in the next lesson } 5...
d6 { It is not so easy for White to get something special. } 6. c3
{ This used to be considered the best, but in the age of computers, Black holds here. }
6... Nxe4 7. d4 Bd7 8. Re1 Nf6
{ This position used to be considered better for White, but nowadays computers are holding here, and Black has just enough to equalize here.  Therefore, I'm not sure after 6.c3 Nxe4 White can pretend to have any sort of advantage; play becomes very forced and it seems if Black knows what he's doing he will equalize finally. }
