3... a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O
{ Here are a lot of main systems that I will explain in the next lesson } 5...
d6 { It is not so easy for White to get something special. } 6. Bxc6+ bxc6 7.
d4 { 7.Re1  c5  8.c3  Now Black has  8...Bg4  . } 7... exd4
{ We obtain a system derived from the Berlin and I'm not sure if White will get anything here. }
8. Nxd4
{ I prefer to capture with the knight as it is more serious than  8.Qxd4  . }
8... c5 9. Nc6 Qd7 10. Na5 Qa4
{ A direct game, it is difficult to see if White can have an advantage. I believe that according to modern theory, Black has chances to equalize. }
