1. --
{ In this lesson I’ve shown you my preferred ways of dealing with early deviations by Black in the Spanish, but there are multiple good ways of answering them, and you can study these variations and find your own way of playing as White against them.The lines shown in this lesson are not very popular, but most of them are not that bad, so you do need to know as White what to do against them. As Black, most of the variations shown in this chapter are playable, but you need to understand that White can usually get at least a small advantage against them. These are not the lines that have caused many White players to give up the Ruy Lopez in favor of the Italian.   In the next two lessons we will consider the main alternative to @@StartFEN@@r1bqkbnr/pppp1ppp/2n5/1B2p3/4P3/5N2/PPPP1PPP/RNBQK2R b KQkq - 3 3@@EndFEN@@  3...a6  , and one which has caused White a lot of problems over the past 20 years: the Berlin or  3...Nf6  . }
*

