4. d3
{ The serious move. When I prepared Berlin against Garry Kasparov for our match, I was pretty sure that he was not going to play d3 because it's not in the concept of his play. He always tried to play the main line to fight for an opening advantage to play in a very principled way with White. Playing d3 gives Black lots of different choices, he can play d6-Bc5 and there is no way White can be much better here.  But I realized that things are not so easy here and I spent quite some time actually trying to find the best weapon against d3. So it is a serious move. Black's two main options are  4...Bc5  or  4...d6  , where Bc5 is more principled and more popular among top players nowadays. }
4... d6
{ This is very playable for Black and you need to know much less theory compared to Bc5. But of course, after d6 White also has a kind of normal Ruy Lopez with certain chances for an opening advantage or complicated games. So d6 is not a refutation of d3.   If you want really to play in a very principled way, probably you should rather play the  4...Bc5  variation but from time to time, especially in rapid time control, I played d6 and I can say that it's perfectly playable.So now White has a choice and it is quite important here to understand the move order. }
5. c3
{ The simplest for White is to play  c3  here right away, but that gives Black a chance to play  5...Be7  and that will transpose to the other line. }
5... g6
{ This is a quite serious difference compared to @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/ppp2ppp/2np1n2/1B2p3/4P3/3P1N2/PPP2PPP/RNBQK2R w KQkq - 0 5@@EndFEN@@  5.O-O  because then g6 doesn't work so well. }
6. O-O Bg7 7. Re1 O-O 8. Nbd2 a6 9. Ba4
{ This is a complicated position. Of course. Black already has a bishop on g7, which improves his typical Ruy Lopez, but still, it's all about Black sooner or later getting d5 as very often is the main idea for Black in the Ruy Lopez in general, and in these types of positions but it's not easy to manage as the e5-pawn is hanging.So I would say it's a complicated game, playable for White and nothing bad for Black but it depends on your taste. But if I would have to choose between White or Black I would definitely take White here as it's not the kind of clear cut way for Black to equalize. }
