{ There is a lot of theory and I will not show you all the lines because there are many, but there is not the slightest danger. You just have to study it and check with engines. I played this once in 2001 against Ivanchuk and I managed to win - it was an absolutely crazy game at the time. The theory was not developed yet and, with no time increment, we had like two minutes for 20 moves and it was a terrible time scramble. Finally, I managed to win it. It is already established quite clearly that taking this pawn is good for Black. }
