7. Bg5
{ Also similar to the Italian, White is trying to pin this knight on f6. In my opinion, this is much less dangerous than in Italian when the white bishop is on c4. }
7... h6 8. Bh4 g5 9. Bg3
{ Again, a similar position but here the main difference is that Black has Nh5. }
9... Nh5
{ As you know from the Italian when Black manages to get Nh5 in this type of position, he's okay. }
10. Nxe5 Nxg3 11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. Bxc6 Nxf1 { And Black is doing fine here. } *

