{ I played a few games here, and you need to study it by checking move for move because, in this type of position, it's very important for White to get his knight to g3 with a Be3 setup, where he has the center and the better position. So Black has to be very careful always to meet Nf1 with d5 here to be always ready to get d5 under favorable circumstances. Sometimes it works, sometimes it doesn't work.So that's why it's all about this whole battle here in this position, I analyzed it a lot, trying to make sure that in this position, which is a very important position in this variation, that I'm always in time to get d5. }
12. Bc2 Bc7 13. a4 a5
{ So it's a kind of zugzwang, as White doesn't really have a move in this position. If  14.b3  , then  14...d5  works. }
14. Nf1 d5 { This is enough to equalize. } *

