7. Re1 Ne7 8. d4 Bb6
{ it seems that White has nothing better than Nbd2 which will transpose to the 7. Nbd2 line.   In case of  9.dxe5  , Black has  9...Ng4  and if @@StartFEN@@r1bq1rk1/ppp1nppp/1b1p1n2/1B2p3/3PP3/2P2N2/PP3PPP/RNBQR1K1 w - - 1 9@@EndFEN@@  9.Bd3  immediately here, then  9...Nc6  is good.  10.d5  Ne7  . }
9. Nbd2
