{ White has some issues protecting the center because Black has active pieces, and a lot of pressure, trying to get Bg4-Ng6 sometimes d5-e5-Ne4 ideas. I don't know what the modern engine is saying about it, but I remember analyzing it a lot and sometimes the game will get very complicated actually very double-edged - you can really play for the win here as Black. }
10. h3 d5 11. e5 Ne4 12. Qe2 Bf5 13. Bd3 Nc6
{ And it seems that White has nothing better than all these exchanges on e4. The position is very drawish after that. }
