[Round "?"]
[White "Lesson 19: Spanish, Berlin with 4. O-O"]
[Black "Spanish Berlin 4. O-O Nxe4, 5. d4, 6. Bxc6 #9"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. O-O
{ The main line of the Berlin Defense, where Black should take the pawn. } 4...
Nxe4 { The best and probably only move to fight for equality. } 5. d4
{ The main move in the position and practically the most dangerous. } 5... Nd6
{ 5...Be7  is possible, but we will not go into that any further. } 6. Bxc6
dxc6 7. dxe5 Nf5 8. Qxd8+ Kxd8
