6... Nc5 7. Bxc6 dxc6 8. Nxe5
{ Normally, with two bishops, Black should be OK and the only question is whether White can pose some immediate problems. In the long-term, Black is doing well.   8.d4  e4  seems to work well for Black. }
8... Be6 9. Qh5 Qe7 10. d4 Nd7
{ It's possible to analyze this further, though Black should of course be fine. }
*

