{ This is one of the main lines according to the engine. } 18... Bxd4 19. cxd4
Ng6 20. Kh1 Nhf4
{ Play is not obvious at all. White has two bishops and is two pawns up, but what can we say? According to the computer, Black apparently has enough counterplay. }
21. Be3
{ This is the main move. Now Black can recapture one of the sacrificed pawns. }
21... Rxb2
{ Black has enough play for the pawn to make a draw, but no more than that. } *

