15. Nc3
{ The aforementioned computers found this move. White is just playing for compensation. You need to analyze this position on your own. There are not many human games from this position, but the computer statistics are frightening - about 70% in White's favor!Purely looking at the position, this is understandable, as White has a very dangerous initiative. The bishop on a7 is very difficult to get into play, while the bishop on b3 is on a very powerful diagonal. }
