{ This seems the most accurate move order, instead of the immediate  14...g5  . }
15. cxd4 g5 16. Nxg5 hxg5 17. Bxg5 Nxd4
{ You'll need to check with an engine why this version is not so bad for Black. I guess that  18.Bd5  ,  which was a problem previously, is not so dangerous anymore as the rook on b8 protects the bishop on b7. It's very tactical. }
