{ This is the old mainline of 7. Bc2. Instead, recently White has been trying to achieve something with the move  10.dxc5  . After  10...Nd3  the position becomes very unbalanced. I think Black is holding, but again, the position is very concrete and difficult to play over the board, so you need to make sure that you analyze it with the computer beforehand. }
