15. d4 { As  15.Nh2  runs into  15...d5  ,  White usually pushes d4 here. }
15... cxd4 { However, Black can just exchange a bunch. } 16. cxd4 exd4 17. Nxd4
Nxd4 18. Qxd4 Rc8
{ Here Black has enough resources to equalize. I had a game against Christopher Lutz here in 2003 or 2004. It's fine for Black. }
19. Bb3 d5
{ This is enough to equalize. So 11. Nbd2 is quite harmless in my opinion. } *

