8... Be6
{ This is a quite playable option. Black's idea is that it doesn't make much sense for White to exchange on e6 in conjunction with the move a2-a3. }
9. Bxe6 fxe6
{ Now after e.g.  10.c3  we get a position where White is practically a tempo down, as the most logical way for White to continue is a4  @@StartBracket@@but he has already played a3@@EndBracket@@. Since he is a tempo down, it shouldn't be anything special for White. }
