15. Nxe7+ Qxe7 16. Qg3
{ When this variation was first played, White would play like this and start to push the f-pawn. }
16... Rac8 17. f4 c5
{ White tries to keep the pawn structure intact and will then go for Rae1 and e5. Black needs to be careful, but this position isn't something special for White. }
18. Ba2
{ Then keeping this pawn structure and trying to go for Rae1 and e5. There is some danger for Black but it shouldnt be something very special for White. }
