9. Nc3
{ Now we arrive at the tabiya of this variation. Here Black has a huge choice. I believe that for Black, my recommendation would be to choose at least one, maybe two of these lines, and analyze them thoroughly.Aronian has played this position a lot as Black, but he jumps around a lot between different moves that Black can try after 9. Nc3. This is because, while it seems that almost every variation is valid, from time to time some problems occur in a specific variation - so Black can then switch to a different variation.But, with good opening preparation, I think that you'll manage to equalize as Black here. Which line to choose depends on your taste. Do you want clear-cut equality? Do you want a more complicated game? }
