8. c3 { This is the main line. } 8... O-O { Now White has a choice. } 9. h3
{ This is by far the most popular move and the main line of the entire variation. White prevents Bg4. In my opinion, this is much more dangerous than playing for d4 immediately. }
9... Na5
{ In the 60s, 70s and 80s, the so-called Chigorin variation, starting with the move Na5, was very popular. Karpov, in particular, was very successful from the White side, winning many classic games. }
10. Bc2 c5 11. d4
{ I believe @@StartBracket@@and computers confirm this assessment@@EndBracket@@that Black doesn't have full equality here. Of course, there are many different systems, but none of them - in my opinion - equalize. That doesn't mean that they aren't playable - in fact, a number of top players employ them from time to time. But even so, I would be very happy to play this as White in every game. Nowadays, it is very difficult to gain anything out of the opening and in this line, White has significant chances of obtaining an actual opening advantage. }
11... Qc7 { This is the main move in the position. } 12. Nbd2
{ The main line for White is tried and tested way of posing problems to Black. Black has tried many different ways of playing and they are all playable, but in every line the statistic is heavily in White's favour. }
12... Nc6
{ This system involving the retreat of the knight to d8 was popular some time ago. }
13. d5 Nd8
{ This system was discovered by Akiba Rubinstein and was considered playable for a long time. Rubinstein was trying to execute the plan of  14.--  g6  15.--  Ne8  16.--  g7  17.--  Ng7  18.--  f5  .  It is actually a very good plan, but it takes a lot of time to execute it, which gives White enough chances to start the play of their own. }
14. a4
{ Nowadays, immediate counterplay on the queenside is considered as clearly better for White. }
14... Rb8 15. b4
{ And White will get play along the open a-file and Black will not be in time to execute the aforementioned plan. This is why I don't recommend you this opening variation if you are considering it with Black. }
