18. axb5 { Here again White has a number of options. } 18... axb5 19. Nd4
{ One of the most direct attempts. } 19... Rxa3 20. bxa3 Nd3 21. Bxd3 cxd3
{ This is all still part of theory. } 22. Bb2 Qa5
{ And this type of position is very dangerous for Black because if White manages to pick up the pawn on d3 and get the knight to f5, things might go wrong quickly for Black. But it seems that Black might be holding here in computer games @@StartBracket@@even though I am not 100% sure because new engines might change the assessment of such a position@@EndBracket@@. }
*

