16. Qf1 { 16.Bxg5  Qf5  is a successful double attack. } 16... Qh5 17. Nd2
{ Computers also started playing, in a more positional manner. } 17... Bh3
{ 17...f5  is sharp and needs to be analyzed. I am not sure it gives enough compensation. }
18. Qe2 Qg6 19. Nf3 f6
{ Followed by ...Kg8-h8/ g7 with quite decent statistics. In general, in Marshall lines where the pawn is on d4, Black often doesn't need to rush in order to prove compensation but can just play positionally. Engines for instance often play the move ... a6-a5-a4, which seems slow but is a sound positional idea. }
