1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 O-O
{ White's main alternatives to  8.c3  are  8.a4  ,  8.h3  , and  8.d4  , which we will examine one by one. }
8. d4 { An important move, that needs to be studied. } 8... Nxd4
{ This move equalizes in very direct fashion and is the reason this line isn't seen much at the top level anymore. }
9. Nxd4 exd4 10. e5 Ne8 11. c3
{ The critical way of playing from White's side. Many games were played here at the top level. And once again I should mention Levon Aronian as one of the experts to follow. }
11... c5 { This may not be bad at all. } 12. cxd4 c4 13. Bc2 d5 14. Nc3 Nc7
{ White has some initiative but computer statistics are not so bad at all. This may well be playable. }
