{ Here Black needs to be a bit careful. If White manages to develop the queenside with Qd1-e2, Bc1-e3, Nb1-d2 it may get unpleasant. For now, White is far from reaching this setup though and Black should be in time to create play. }
12. Qe2 a5 13. Nd2 Bc5 14. Nc4 Qe7
{ White has a little bit of pressure, and the better pawn structure, but it's nothing special. Knowing this position well with Black should guarantee that there is little to fear. }
