[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 O-O
{ White's main alternatives to  8.c3  are  8.a4  ,  8.h3  , and  8.d4  , which we will examine one by one. }
8. a4
{ Maybe the most popular move to avoid the Marshall and, in my opinion, the most interesting way to do so too. In this line there are still some small problems to solve for Black here and there. }
8... b4
{ The most popular move in the position and a bit more direct than  8...Bb7  which I consider to be completely fine as well. This move has been analyzed considerably more compared to 8...Bb7 but it's hard for me to make a distinction of one over the other. }
9. c3 { Not very fashionable. } 9... d5
{ Very fine in this version. I am not even sure if after  9...d6  ,  the inclusion of a2-a4 and ...b5-b4 is in White's favor. }
10. exd5 Nxd5 11. Nxe5 Nxe5 12. Rxe5 Bb7
{ White's issue is that the queenside is hard to develop. Even  12...Be6  is quite OK. }
13. Qf3 Bd6
{ An important idea! After  14.Rxd5  there are ideas like  14...Re8  . } 14.
Bxd5 c6 15. Re2 cxd5 { Black has good compensation. } *

