14. h3 Rb8 15. Ng3 a5 16. Nf5 Bc8
{ Computers are playing it very cool here. They don't mind having the knight on f5, or potentially losing the bishop pair if White takes on e7. Well, who am I to judge? :@@EndBracket@@ }
